for satisfying aesthetic experience. Anyway, as soon as a generation of <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">artists</ENAMEX>
or connoisseurs declares for one, the gauntlet is dropped, and the next will
plumb for the other.

            Incidentally, you do subscribe to one
<ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">formalist</ENAMEX> dogma. The insistence that one must see an exhibition before
having anything critical to say about ideas and images within it attributes a
great importance to the visceral experience of objects, an attendance to form.
